## Setup

  1. Clone the template into a new project folder:
     git clone https://github.com/yairharel81/web-llm-project-template-v1.git taskflow
     cd taskflow

  2. Start infrastructure (Postgres + Redis):
     docker compose up -d

  3. Set up the backend:
     cd backend
     python3 -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
     pip install -e .
     cp ../.env.example .env
     alembic upgrade head
     cd ..

  4. Set up the frontend:
     cd frontend && npm install && cd ..

  5. Set up Playwright (first time only):
     cd tests/e2e && npm install && npx playwright install chromium && cd ../..

  Now read CLAUDE.md and README.md before writing any code. They tell you
  exactly which files to touch for each type of change.

  ---

  ## App: TaskFlow — Team Task Manager

  ### What to build
  A multi-user task management app where users can:
  1. Create projects (a named container for tasks)
  2. Create tasks inside projects (title, description, priority: low/medium/high,
     due date, assignee)
  3. Assign tasks to other registered users
  4. Update task status (todo → in_progress → done)
  5. Receive a real-time SSE notification when they are assigned a new task
  6. Get an email (via Brevo) when they are assigned a task
  7. Ask the built-in AI assistant (Gemini) to summarize all open tasks in a
     project as a daily briefing

  ### Backend requirements
  - New database tables: Project, Task (with FK to Project and User),
    ProjectMember join table (users can belong to multiple projects)
  - REST endpoints:
    - POST   /api/v1/projects              — create project
    - GET    /api/v1/projects              — list my projects
    - POST   /api/v1/projects/{id}/tasks   — create task in project
    - GET    /api/v1/projects/{id}/tasks   — list tasks in project
    - PATCH  /api/v1/tasks/{id}/status     — update status
    - POST   /api/v1/projects/{id}/summary — AI summary of open tasks
  - Publish SSE event type "task_assigned" when a task is assigned to a user
  - Send a Brevo email on assignment using the email service

  ### Frontend requirements
  - /projects page: list projects, create project button
  - /projects/:id page: task list with 3 kanban columns (todo / in_progress / done),
    create task form with assignee dropdown (project members only)
  - Toast notification when a "task_assigned" SSE event arrives (use useSSEEvent)
  - AI Summary button on the project page that calls /summary and shows the
    result in a modal

  ### Rules
  - Read CLAUDE.md before touching any file — follow every pattern already in
    the template, do not invent new ones
  - Use the existing mock/real service pattern for Gemini and email
  - Use useSSEEvent() for real-time events, never useSSE() inside pages
  - Do not modify any existing auth, user, or core infrastructure files
  - Run alembic migrations after adding models

  ---

  ## Deliver

  When done, list every file created or modified.

  Start both servers:
     # Terminal 1 — backend
     cd backend && source .venv/bin/activate && uvicorn app.main:app --reload

     # Terminal 2 — frontend
     cd frontend && npm run dev

  Run the full Playwright suite — all tests must pass before declaring done:
     cd tests/e2e && npx playwright test

  The suite already covers baseline auth. Add a new spec file for your feature
  tests (do not modify auth.spec.ts). Provide the final test output showing
  all tests passing and the local URLs:
  - Frontend:        http://localhost:5173
  - Backend API docs: http://localhost:8000/docs

